cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper addresses the problem of unsupervised object localization in single images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper employs region proposals and saliency maps, which are commonly used in object detection and segmentation tasks, indicating that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves evaluating the method's performance on a benchmark dataset, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which is a common theme in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
